	<h1>Data Visualisation</h1>
	<p aligh=justify>
		Visualizing data helps to get a better understanding of the data.
		<br> Here is a dashboard/workbook representing the Monroe Crash data.
		<br>
		<br><strong> Doughnut chart : Collision-Type- Represents the count of crashs summarized by collision Types.</strong>
		<br> The collision types include: 2 cars, 3 cars, Bus , Cyclist , Motorcycle.
		<br>
		<br><strong> Doughnut chart : Year- Shows the count of crashes over the years. </strong>
		<br> Years : 2011,2012,2013,2014,2015,2016,2017
		<br>
		<br><strong> Piechart : Injury-Type- Represents the count of crashs summarized by Injury Types.</strong>
		<br> The Injury types include: Fatal,No-Injury,Incapacitating , Unknown .
		<br>
		<br><strong> Piechart : Crash Count by Hours- Represents the count of crashs occured across time.</strong>


	</p>


